reviews.review_text: Spend the Cash I was hoping for a little better sound than this. I applaud the effort but I think you'd be better off just getting the DP 30. I'll just get the flac version from dead.net.
gem priceless gem!!  does anyone know if a soundboard even exists?  the content here deserves 5 stars but because it's an audience tape, it gets only 3.

You Know I Love You It's tragic that the sound quality renders this recording rather difficult to enjoy. Track 6 is a beautiful ten-minute jam that certainly should have been included on Dick's Picks #30. I love the Bo Diddley set and I'll give this file  three stars for the sublime Wow Wow Hey Hey.

Boo Hoo I just want to cry that Sitting On Top Of The World isn't on DP30, it was so rarely done. What a ballsy skkkkorcher was thine!!! Alas, twas not to be.  That (marred by feedback) Slow Blues and Pollution with Bo are just sooo freaking fabulous!  Even with a slightly problematic Slow Blues, why in god's name would anybody need one more OMSN, BEW, PITB, or SugMag??? Dick (RIP), yah goofed.  Anybody know if those two might have been featured on the Dead Hour?

*Update - Found "Sitting" and those sweet Bo Diddley blues tunes a few months ago on the internet and recorded the stream.  Definitely worth the search.
- I'm sure this rocks, if I could hear it...
